{what is Nimzowitsch and how to play it} 1. e4 Nc6 {hardly ever played; fights
for central dark squares without yet moving pawns} 2. d4 (2. Nf3 e5 {can
transpose to many main e4-e5 openings}  (2... d6 {Williams variation, avoids e5
theory} 3. d4 Nf6 {keep developing} 4. e5 {big mistake}  (4. d5 Ne5) 4... dxe5
5. dxe5 {d file willt open at some point} 5... Qxd1+ 6. Kxd1 Ng4 7. Ke1 Ngxe5
{up a pawn} )  (2... f5 {Colorado countergambit, fun for quicker time controls}
3. exf5 d5 4. g4 { better to play Bb4 and give pawn back} 4... h5 {black is
better as white kingside is way too overextended} 5. gxh5 (5. h3 {holds pawn
but loses rook} 5... hxg4 6. hxg4 Rxh1) 5... Bxf5 {h5 is still very weak} ) ) 
2... e5 {Kennedy variation}  (2... d5 {Scandinavian variation} 3. exd5 (3. e5
Bf5 {e6 would be even worse than real "french bishop"} 4. Nf3 e6 5. Bd3 Nge7
{dont want to take and let white develop easier} 6. O-O Qd7 7. c3 f6 8. Bxf5
Nxf5 9. exf6 gxf6 {with strong open g file and Bd6} ) 3... Qxd5 {puts a bunch
of pressure on d4} 4. Nf3 e5 {even more pressure} 5. Nc3 Bb4 6. Bd2 Bxc3 7.
Bxc3 e4 {simple chess} ) 3. d5 {60% of online games, black wants to get Ng6
asap}  (3. Nf3 {Scotchs game, but with this start white player is probably not 
a Scotchs player} 3... exd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 {if white exchanges knights,
capture towards center} 5... Bb4 6. Nxc6 bxc6 {Qe7, d5 castling} )  (3. dxe5 d6
{transposes to Charlick gambit} 4. exd6 Bxd6 {down a pawn, but with rapid
development} 5. Nf3 Nf6 {black is down a pawn but develops faster} 6. Nc3 Qe7
7. Bd3 Bg4 8. O-O O-O-O 9. h3 h5 10. hxg4 {Bg5 Ne5 is most popular in online
games, giving black objectively better position} 10... hxg4 {rook is a monster
now} 11. Nd2 Qe5 {threats mate in one} 12. f4 Bc5+ 13. Rf2 Qh5 14. Kf1
{beautiful forced mate} 14... Qh1+ 15. Ke2 Nd4+ 16. Ke3 Nf5+ 17. Ke2 Ng3#) 3...
Nce7 4. c4 Ng6 5. Nc3 Bc5 6. Nf3 Nf6 7. Bd3 {white most popular moves} 7... a5
{key idea! d6 early would trap bishop to Na4} 8. O-O d6 9. a3 O-O {Na4-f4 is a
treat, while g3 makes white squares weak } 10. Bg5 h6 11. Be3 b6 {capturing
allows white to control f4} 12. Bxc5 bxc5 13. Nb5 {most popular for some
reason} 13... Nh5 {or Nh7-g5} 14. Nxe5 {does not work for white:} 14... Nxe5
15. Qxh5 Bg4 {traps queen or Nd3 bishop hanging } *

